'''Dennis Michael Wright Jr.''' (born January 3, 1990) is an American [[professional baseball]] [[pitcher]] in the [[Seattle Mariners]] organization. He has previously played in [[Major League Baseball]] (MLB) for the [[Baltimore Orioles]] and [[Seattle Mariners]].

==Career==
Wright was drafted by the [[Baltimore Orioles]] in the third round of the [[2011 Major League Baseball Draft]] out of [[East Carolina University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reflector.com/sports/ecu/ecursquos-wright-snared-orioles-draft-527733|title=ECU’s Wright snared by Orioles in draft|work=The Daily Reflector|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masnsports.com/steve_melewski/2011/08/os-3rd-round-pick-got-his-feet-wet-at-aberdeen-before-moving-to-delmarva.html|title=Steve Melewski: O's third-round pick got his feet wet at Aberdeen before moving to Delmarva|work=MASNsports|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref> During his first professional season he went 3-2 with a 5.72 [[earned run average]] with 42 strikeouts in {{frac|45|2|3}} innings. Pitching for the [[Frederick Keys]] and [[Bowie Baysox]] in 2012 he went 10-5 with a 4.06 ERA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masnsports.com/steve_melewski/2013/01/checking-on-another-pitching-prospect-a-look-at-right-hander-mike-wright.html|title=Steve Melewski: Checking on another pitching prospect: A look at right-hander Mike Wright|work=MASNsports|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref>

Wright started the 2013 season with Baysox.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masnsports.com/steve_melewski/2013/08/wright-gets-on-a-roll-at-bowie.html|title=Steve Melewski: Wright gets on a roll at Bowie|work=MASNsports|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref> He finished the season with the [[Norfolk Tides]]. He was the [[Jim Palmer]] Minor League Pitcher of the Year Award after going 11–3 with a 3.11 ERA and 138 strikeouts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://baltimore.orioles.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20130907&content_id=59912760&vkey=pr_bal&c_id=bal|title=Orioles announce 2013 Award Winners for Player Development and Scouting|work=Baltimore Orioles|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2013-09-08/sports/bal-urrutia-wright-win-top-minor-league-awards-20130908_1_henry-urrutia-triple-a-norfolk-double-a-bowie|title=Urrutia, Wright win top minor league awards|work=tribunedigital-baltimoresun|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref> He returned to Norfolk to start the 2014 season.

===2015===
Wright made his first career major league start on [[2015 Baltimore Orioles season#Game log|May 17, 2015]] against the [[2015 Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim season|Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim]]. He went {{frac|7|1|3}} innings, striking out 6, allowed 4 hits, no runs, and no walks in order to get the win, 3-0. In 12 games, 9 of them starts, Wright went 3-5 with a 6.04 ERA in {{frac|44|2|3}} innings.

===2016===
Wright was named the Orioles fourth starter at the conclusion of Spring Training. He began in the rotation but struggled and was sent down to the minors. He split time between the O's rotation and the AAA level. In 18 games for the Orioles, 12 of them being in the rotation, Wright went 3-4 with a 5.79 ERA in {{frac|74|2|3}} innings. 

===2017===
Wright spent the majority of the season at the AAA level, receiving a callup to the Majors towards the end of the season. He finished with a 5.76 ERA in 13 games.

===2018===
Wright pitched exclusively out of the bullpen for the O's, totaling 48 appearances. He finished with {{frac|84|1|3}} innings pitched.

===2019===
Wright was on the Opening day roster for the Orioles. He had an ERA of 9.45 through 10 appearances. On April 21, 2019, Wright was designated for assignment to make space for [[Gabriel Ynoa]] on the roster.

===Seattle Mariners===
On April 24, 2019, he was traded to the [[Seattle Mariners]] for infielder Ryne Ogren.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlbtraderumors.com/2019/04/mariners-acquire-mike-wright.html|title=Mariners Acquire Mike Wright|work=MLB Trade Rumors|last=Todd|first=Jeff|date=April 24, 2019|accessdate=April 24, 2019}}</ref> He was designated for assignment on May 19, 2019. On June 23, his contract was selected.<ref>{{cite news|author=RotoWire Staff|title=Mariners' Mike Wright Jr.: Returns to big leagues|url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/baseball/news/mariners-mike-wright-jr-returns-to-big-leagues/|accessdate=June 23, 2019|publisher=CBS Sports|date=June 23, 2019}}</ref> On July 5, he was designated for assignment.<ref>{{cite news|author=Seattle Mariners|title=Right-handed Pitcher Mike Wright is designated for assignment|url=https://www.mlb.com/mariners/press-release/rhp-matt-wisler-reports-rhp-mike-wright-dfa?t=mariners-press-releases|accessdate=July 5, 2019|publisher=MLB.com|date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>

===Pitching Style===
Wright throws 5 pitches: a four seam fastball that averages around 96 MPH, a sinker at around 93, a changeup at around 82, a slider at about 86, and a curveball at around 75.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brooksbaseball.net/velo.php?player=605541&b_hand=-1&gFilt=&pFilt=FA%7cSI%7cFC%7cCU%7cSL%7cCS%7cKN%7cCH%7cFS%7cSB&time=month&minmax=ci&var=mph&s_type=2&startDate=03/30/2007&endDate=05/18/2015|title=Player Card: Mike Wright|work=brooksbaseball.net|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref>

